<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#F0DCA0">Originally posted by lar on 10-24-99 08:05 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Wow, last time I got such a list of questions was when I was applying for a loan to create this game ;) Let's see, I could answer with no comments, I could be very vague, or I could just start answering them...hmmm...

Well, I'm not saying if it is a CRPG or not, as I never did understand the exact definition of that word anyway. So definitely no comment on the CRPG thing. You see, I once witnessed a discussion that deteriorated rather quickly in a full fledged war over the meaning of CRPG, and I don't want to be in it. However, it's a game were you control  a hero or heroin, and he/she gets involved in this story and she/he needs to do something by interacting with her/his environment which is the game world. That rather describes it accurately.

1) Who said anything about combat ;) Real time I guess, though how can one talk about real time when talking about a computer game ???

2)Well that's a bit difficult. Obviously you are controlling somebody. If you interact smart, you might control more than one somebody. Maybe the somebody you control is schizophrenic ;)

3) Ah, I think in the past I made it quite clear that I hate level systems, so I would never want to be caught making one ;)
4) That kinda depends on 2), doesn't it ? 
5) Ouch ouch ouch.  Another inter-dependency in the questioning. I won't answer directly, but I'll tell you this, you'll have a way of researching certain things, just like in most real time strategy games. The way you research things will definitely have an effect on your gameplay.
6) Madness as technically speaking it might be neverending ;) But that's very vague ;)
7) You'll have to wait and see, but yes, I think you'll find it quite original. I can't really comment on that because discovering the story is part of the fun. As a matter of fact, I can't even tell you anything about the beginning, as even that would take away from your fun. 
8) If only I knew ;) Seriously, we are aiming very hard at having it ready this year, with a release somewhere in the second quarter of next year (testing, localization etc..), or if we're lucky, in the first quarter. Apart from some features, the game is playable now, but we'll only know during this week as that is when our major build should be complete. Once that is done, we'll release the first shots etc... However, we only have two more months to reach our self appointed deadline, so I don't want to pin ourselves on it. But you'll see. I really promise that we'll give away info the moment we can. Right now we can't, and that has a lot to do with the build we need to finalize.
9) No comment ;)

Lar


</TEXTAREA>
